  • Handle: @gecko-template
  • Preview:
    • With layout
    • Component only
  • Filesystem Path: components/components/forms/gecko-template/gecko-template.twig

Gecko template

This is flat HTML taken from a Gecko embed, it shows how the HTML of different fields and field states will look in an embedded form. This is to be used for initial local developement.

NB the fields are just visuals, fields that required JS won’t work and the form doesn’t submit. The preview uses the gecko wrapper which is set up to replicate how an embedded form loads, with the Gecko styles loading first, followed by our CSS.

Gecko have opted not to use fieldset and legend tags for their radio/checkbox groups. Instead they use a label tag for the group with is subsequently orphaned. They said after running through a checker the orphaned tag is flagged just as an advisory.
